One of the single most core aspects of my framework, that which acts as a foundation for much of the rest, is that of the connection of EVP with 'the voice' or what might be called the language faculty. The fact that all the aspects associated with EVP, including the cognition of themes as meaningful structural entities such that their incompleteness demands further resolution, that such resolution is sought through a demand to return to what is perceived as a tonic note whose satisfaction is suspended, that themes are specifically felt to be modified through 'canonical transformations', that music being perceived in polyphony and counterpoint as individual voices 'communicating' with each other is only possible in association with this, and that this complex of structural and perceptual aspects should in principle show up on brain scans (particularly fMRI), such that people who are capable of this demonstrate mental activity in areas associated with language processing while people who aren't do not do so in the same way, which I believe has been shown to be the case in existing studies, is in its essence a backbone to the significance of most of what I am conjecturing.}
